<script lang="ts">
  const html: string = "<h1>Data Table Row</h1>\n\n<p>A data table row represents a single row within a data table, typically corresponding to one record. It wraps data cells or header cells in a horizontal sequence. It is designed to be used inside a DataTableHead, DataTableBody, or DataTableFoot section.</p>\n\n<p>The component renders a <code>&lt;tr&gt;</code> element and passes through its children, which are expected to be <code>&lt;td&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;th&gt;</code>, or DataTableTD elements.</p>\n\n<h2>Implementation Notes</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Renders as a <code>&lt;tr&gt;</code> element for one row in a data table</li>\n<li>Children should be data cells (<code>&lt;td&gt;</code> or DataTableTD) or header cells (<code>&lt;th&gt;</code>)</li>\n<li>Designed to be used inside DataTableHead, DataTableBody, or DataTableFoot</li>\n<li>Spreads <code>restProps</code> onto the <code>&lt;tr&gt;</code> element for consumer customization</li>\n<li>No internal state -- purely a structural wrapper</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Props</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><code>children</code>: slot (required) -- cells for this row</li>\n<li><code>...restProps</code>: Any additional HTML attributes passed to the <code>&lt;tr&gt;</code> element</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n\n<pre><code class=\"language-html\">&lt;DataTableBody&gt;\n  &lt;DataTableRow&gt;\n    &lt;td&gt;Alice&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;alice@example.com&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Admin&lt;/td&gt;\n  &lt;/DataTableRow&gt;\n  &lt;DataTableRow&gt;\n    &lt;td&gt;Bob&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;bob@example.com&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Editor&lt;/td&gt;\n  &lt;/DataTableRow&gt;\n&lt;/DataTableBody&gt;</code></pre>\n\n<h2>Keyboard Interactions</h2>\n\n<p>None -- this component is a passive container. Navigation within the table follows standard browser behavior.</p>\n\n<h2>ARIA</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Implicit <code>row</code> role from the <code>&lt;tr&gt;</code> element -- identifies a row of cells within the table</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>When to Use</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Use inside DataTable to provide the <code>&lt;tr&gt;</code> row element within DataTableHead, DataTableBody, or DataTableFoot.</li>\n<li>Use for each record or header row in a data table.</li>\n<li>Use when you need to spread additional attributes like event handlers or data attributes onto a <code>&lt;tr&gt;</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>When Not to Use</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Do not use outside DataTable -- use TableRow, CalendarTableRow, GanttTableTR, or KanbanTableRow for their respective table types.</li>\n<li>Do not use as a standalone element -- it requires a parent <code>&lt;thead&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;tbody&gt;</code>, or <code>&lt;tfoot&gt;</code> for valid HTML.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Headless</h2>\n\n<p>This headless DataTableRow component provides a semantic <code>&lt;tr&gt;</code> element with implicit <code>row</code> role for assistive technology. The consumer provides all visual styling including hover highlights, selected-row states, striped row backgrounds, and click interaction styles.</p>\n\n<h2>Styles</h2>\n\n<p>The consumer provides all CSS styling. The component renders with a <code>.data-table-row</code> class for targeting. No default styles are included — this is a fully headless component.</p>\n\n<h2>Testing</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Verify the component renders a <code>&lt;tr&gt;</code> element with class <code>data-table-row</code></li>\n<li>Verify pass-through attributes are applied</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Advice</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Designers</strong>: Use hover highlights to help users track which row they are reading. Consider a selected-row state for interactive tables.</li>\n<li><strong>Developers</strong>: Place <code>&lt;td&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;th&gt;</code>, or DataTableTD elements as children. Use <code>restProps</code> to add click handlers or data attributes for interactive row selection.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Composition</h2>\n\n<p>DataTableRow is part of the DataTable composition pattern. It sits inside DataTableHead, DataTableBody, or DataTableFoot and contains DataTableTD or <code>&lt;th&gt;</code> elements. The full hierarchy is DataTable &gt; DataTableHead/DataTableBody/DataTableFoot &gt; DataTableRow &gt; DataTableTD.</p>\n\n<h2>Related components</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><code>data-table</code> — a data table interactive grid for displaying and sorting tabular data &lt;table&gt;</li>\n<li><code>data-table-body</code> — a data table interactive grid tbody for displaying and sorting tabular data &lt;tbody&gt;</li>\n<li><code>data-table-foot</code> — a data table interactive grid tfoot for displaying and sorting tabular data &lt;tfoot&gt;</li>\n<li><code>data-table-head</code> — a data table interactive grid thead for displaying and sorting tabular data &lt;thead&gt;</li>\n<li><code>data-table-td</code> — a data table interactive grid data cell for displaying and sorting tabular data &lt;td&gt;</li>\n<li><code>data-table-th</code> — a data table interactive grid header cell for displaying and sorting tabular data &lt;th&gt;</li>\n<li><code>table</code> — a table with rows and columns &lt;table&gt;</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>References</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>WAI-ARIA Table Pattern: https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/table/</li>\n<li>WAI Tutorial on Tables: https://www.w3.org/WAI/tutorials/tables/</li>\n</ul>";
</script>

